# # --- Variables in python
#         # Variables in python are used to store the values in the memory location. It is alike a contenor that stores 
#          the value in it. 
            # The vallue of the variable can be changed.
            #(_) is used for the vallue of the previous operatins .
            # To fetch charecter in a string [] this is used.
            # If we use negative number to fetch then it will start counting from the right to left.
            # To take out multiple charecter we use [:] this is used.
            # To get the length of the string we use len() this is used.
            
# # --- List in Python
           # List in python is a collection of the vallue that are  changeable. It means
           # we can change the vallue of the list after we created.
           # List is denoted by using [] this is used.
           # To add two variables we use e.g. x=[variable1,variable2]
           # To add a single variable we use e.g. x.append(variable)
           # To get the vallue we just simply need x.
           # To delete the vallue we use e.g. del x[0]
           # To extend the vallue we use e.g. x.extend([variable])
           # To insert the vallue we use e.g. x.insert(0,variable)
           # To remove the vallue we use e.g. x.remove(variable)
           # To get the minimum number we use e.g. x. min(variable)
           # To get the maximum number we use e.g. x. max(variable)
           # To get the sum of the number we use e.g. x. sum(variable)
           # To sort the number we use e.g. x. sort().
           
# # --- Tuple in Python
           # Tuple in python is a collection of the vallue that are not changeable. It
           # means we can not change the vallue of the tuple after we created.
           # Tuple is denoted by using () this is used.
           # Tuple is faster than list
           
# # --- Dictionary in Python
           # Dictionary in python is a collection of the vallue that are changeable. It
           # means we can change the vallue of the dictionary after we created.
           # Dictionary is denoted by using {} this is used.
           # To add a key and value we use e.g. x[key]=value
           # To get the vallue we use e.g. x[key]
           # To delete the vallue we use e.g. del x[key]
           # we can create the dictionary wit in a dictionary.
           
# # --- More on Variables Memory consumption
            # In memory variables has its own memory location.
            # the memory location of each variable is different unless they have the same data type or name.
            # The memory consumption of the variable depends on the data type of the variable.
            # The memory consumption of the variable is different for different data type.
            # To no the memory location of the variable we use id(variable) this is used.
            # To no the memory consumption of the variable we use sys.getsizeof(variable) this is used.
            # if adata will not be used or tag  then it will be deleted from the memory location and goes to the garbage collection
            # The garbage collection is a process that is used to free the memory location of the variable that
            # is not used or tag. By this way Python is more memory efficient.
            # The garbage collection is done by Python automatically.
            # To know the type of the variable we use type(variable) this is used.
            # We can also change the type of the variable by using typecasting. and we can create our one type.

            
