 # # --- Operators
            # In python we have the following operators
            # 1. Arithmetic operators
            # 2. Relational operators
            # 3. Logical operators
            # 4. Assignment operators
            # 5. Bitwise operators
            # 6. Unary operators
            # Arithmatic operators are used to perform the mathematical operation like addition, subtraction,        multiplication, division etc.
            # Relational operators are used to compare the two values.
            # Logical operators are used to perform the logical operation like and, or, not etc.
            # Assignment operators are used to assign the value to the variable
            # Bitwise operators are used to perform the bitwise operation like and, or, not etc.
            # Unary operators are used to perform the operation on a single operand.
            # The precedency of the operators include Arithmatic operators > Relational operators > Logical operators > Assignment operators > Bitwise operators > Unary operators.
            # The associativity of the operators include Left to right and right to left.
            
 # # --- Number convertion
            # In python we have converted the number from decimal to binary, octal, hexadecimal and vice versa.
            # To convert the number from decimal to binary we use bin() function.
            # To convert the number from decimal to octal we use oct() function.
            # To convert the number from decimal to hexadecimal we use hex() function.
            # To convert binary to decimal we simple use 0b(binary numbere).
            # To convert octal to decimal we simple use 0o(octal number).
            # To convert hexadecimal to decimal we simple use 0x(hexadecimal number).

 # # --- Bitwise operations
            # In python following bit wse operations are used
            # 1. Bitwise AND (&)
            # 2. Bitwise OR (|)
            # 3. Bitwise XOR (^)
            # 4. Bitwise NOT (~) / Bitwise Complement
            # 5. Bitwise Left Shift (<<)
            # 6. Bitwise Right Shift (>>)
            # Bitwise AND (&) is used to perform the AND operation on two bits.
            # Bitwise OR (|) is used to perform the OR operation on two bits.
            # Bitwise XOR (^) is used to perform the XOR operation on two bits.
            # Bitwise NOT (~) / Bitwise Complement is used to perform the NOT operation on a bit.
            # Bitwise Left Shift (<<) is used to shift the bits of the number to left.
            # Bitwise Right Shift (>>) is used to shift the bits of the number to right.
            # The Bitwise operations are used to perform the operation on the binary number.
            # for bit wise left shift we can go as binary vallue and also by mathematical formula
                e.g. 8<<2
                      = 8*2^2.
            # for bit wise right shift we can go as binary vallue and also by mathematical formula
                e.g. 8>>2
                      = 8/2^2.

